and petrochemicals. For example, oxygen is a vital element in the production of fertilizers and other key chemicals, while nitrogen is used as an inert atmosphere in various chemical processes to prevent undesirable reactions. The growing demand for chemicals driven by sectors like agriculture, pharmaceuticals, and automotive has led to a corresponding rise in the need for air separation technologies in the chemical industry. <p>The demand for air separation in the chemical industry is also driven by advancements in technology that enable more energy-efficient and cost-effective production methods. Innovations in cryogenic air separation processes and membrane technology have made it possible to produce higher purity gases at reduced costs, meeting the increasing needs of the chemical industry. With being a significant player in the global chemical market, the demand for reliable and efficient air separation systems will continue to grow. The air separation units serve not only to meet the specific needs of chemical producers but also to support the ongoing trend toward sustainability and energy efficiency in the sector.</p> <p>**Industrial Gas:** The industrial gas segment is another crucial application of air separation systems in Mexico. Industrial gases such as oxygen, nitrogen, and argon play a vital role in a variety of industries, including healthcare, food and beverage, electronics, and manufacturing. In healthcare, oxygen is used in medical applications, including respiratory care and anesthesia, while nitrogen is used for cryogenic applications and in food preservation. In the electronics industry, nitrogen is used for creating controlled environments for semiconductor manufacturing, and in manufacturing, gases like oxygen are used for cutting and welding processes. As industries continue to expand and modernize, the demand for industrial gases produced through air separation will grow. <p>The industrial gas market in has witnessed significant growth due t